But every day I am learning. Growing. Stretching. Becoming.

And most days I can't believe I'm living this dream. These two perfect beings are temporarily mine to watch over, to care for, to nurture.

Seeing them learn.
Watching them discover the world.
Hearing them testing the limits.
Witnessing their innate ability to dream, to trust, to love. 

Some days I wonder why God trusted me to hold their hands and lead them through life. And yet I can't help but think, why not me?

I AM capable. I AM strong. I AM the perfect mom for them.

And if you need that reminder, let this be it. YOU are the mom for your children. You have what it takes. You are strong enough, brave enough, bold enough and valiant.

You are enough. I am enough. We are enough.

